               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1707" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1707" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1707" type="surname" value="IZOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1707" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH IZOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cheesemonger, and live in Blackman-street, in the Borough. On the 28th of March the prisoner came to my shop for half a pound of bacon—it came to 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he gave me a half-crown, which was bad—I told him so, I kept it, and gave it to the officer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1708" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1708" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1708" type="surname" value="READY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1708" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS READY</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 29th of March, between eight and nine o'clock in the evening, the prisoner came to my shop and bought an article, which came to 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he gave me a half-crown—I suspected it was bad, and kept it by itself—I gave him two shillings change, and he left—the policeman came soon afterwards—I marked the half-crown, and gave it him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I called for half a pound of boiled beef. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> Yes, and I had none—then you had roast beef—you were in the shop about five minutes—another man came in while you were there, who I considered was one of your <hi rend="italic">quality</hi>—he tried to attract my attention—I could swear to you.</p>
